write_content_message: Write SEO standard content for the heading {section} located in the article {title}, including 2 to 5 paragraphs, each paragraph at least 300 words and the content should contain one or several keywords: {keywords}. The content must be related to the topic being written, avoid rambling and going off topic. Remove titles and headings. Skip the introduction, go straight to the main point. {rela_section}Format the p tag for the content.
get_title_message: I want to write SEO articles related to keywords: {keywords}. Let's suggest 10 attractive titles in English, each title only needs to be written according to the correct grammar rules: the first letter of the sentence is capitalized, other words are lowercase, and the proper name must keep the correct spelling. Each title should not exceed 70 characters{more}. Return the result as minified JSON, without line breaks, without any characters other than JSON. For example:["Title 1","Title 2", ...]. Make sure to only print the correct JSON, without any additional explanations or quotes.
get_description_message: I want to write an SEO article with the title {title} and related keywords: {keywords}. Suggest 10 attractive descriptions that attract readers by English, each description should be written normally, 2-3 sentences, if it contains keywords, even better {more}. Return the result as minified JSON, no line breaks, no other characters than JSON. For example: ["Description 1","Description 2", ...]. Make sure to print only the JSON, no additional explanation or quotations.
get_section_message: I want to write an SEO article titled {title} and related to the keywords: {keywords}. Please suggest 10 topics in English that should be included in the article, with each topic only needing to be written according to the correct grammar rules: the first letter of a sentence is capitalized, other words are lowercase, and proper names must be kept in the correct spelling. Return the result as minified JSON, without line breaks, without any characters other than JSON. For example: ["Heading 1","Heading 2", ...]. Make sure to only print the correct JSON, without any additional explanations or quotes.
